{{NCAATeamFootballSeason |Year=1998 |Team=Kentucky Wildcats |Image=Uk_logo_preston_ursini.svg |Conference=Southeastern Conference |Division=Eastern Division |ShortConference=SEC |Record=7-5 |ConfRecord=4-4 |CoachRank= |APRank= |HeadCoach=[[Hal Mumme]] |OffCoach= |DefCoach= |OScheme= |DScheme= |StadiumArena=[[Commonwealth Stadium (Kentucky)|Commonwealth Stadium]] |Champion= |BowlTourney=[[1999 Outback Bowl|Outback Bowl]] |BowlTourneyResult=L 26-14 vs. [[1998 Penn State Nittany Lions football team|Penn State]] }} {{1998 SEC football standings}} The '''1998 Kentucky Wildcats football team''' represented the [[University of Kentucky]] in the [[1998 NCAA Division I-A football season]]. [[Quarterback]] [[Tim Couch]] was the first pick overall in the [[1999 NFL Draft]].
==Season== Couch led Kentucky to seven wins, including a win on the road at #21 [[1998 LSU Tigers football team|LSU]] and a spot in the [[1999 Outback Bowl]], where Couch completed 30 of 48 passes for 336 yards and two touchdowns, though Kentucky lost to [[1998 Penn State Nittany Lions football team|Penn State]], 26-14. In the [[KentuckyâLouisville rivalry]], the Wildcats beat the {{cfb link|year=1998|team=Louisville Cardinals|title=Cardinals}} to claim the [[Governor's Cup (Kentucky)|Governor's Cup]]. In the Border Battle, [[1998 Tennessee Volunteers football team|Tennessee]] beat Kentucky by a score of 59-21 to claim the Beer Barrel.<ref>http://mcubed.net/ncaaf/series/tn/ky.shtml</ref>
